Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 805/68 of 27 June 1968 on the common organization of the market in beef and veal (1), as last amended by the Act of Accession of Greece, and in particular Article 12 (7) and Article 25 thereof,
Whereas, because relatively few animals are brought to the market of Hanover, this market can no longer be regarded as representative and should be deleted from the list of representative markets in the Federal Republic of Germany;
Whereas Annexes II and III to Commission Regulation (EEC) No 610/77 (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1458/81 (3), should be amended accordingly;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Beef and Veal,
